<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-07T06:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-07T06:34:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6508: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-07T20:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">March 7,
                                            1920—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 7—12:28
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Last Czech troops left Irkutsk February 25, 6 p.m. Last Czech allies
                                including Servians, Rumanian, Poles, left Irkutsk March 3, 6 p.m.
                                There are 82 Czech and Czech-Allied trains now on Trans-Baikal to be
                                evacuated which may be increased by allotting fewer soldiers to each
                                car. We are trying to evacuate three trains per diem from the
                                Trans-Baikal.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>